{
  "text": "If we extend the flag F \u2022 to a complete flag in Ker(u), then the stabilizer of the extended flag is a Borel subgroup B \u2282 Q. The orbit O \u03c1 is a union of certain Borbits in Gr, that is Schubert cells. So the cardinality of O \u03c1 is a sum of powers of q given by the well known formula for the dimension of the Schubert cells (see e.g. Appendix to Chapter II of [CITATION_1] ). We will denote this cardinality by P \u03c1 . Note that the Jordan type of u| D/W for W \u2208 O \u03c1 is \u03bd \u2032 := \u03c1(\u03bd) where \u03c1(\u03bd) is defined as the partition dual to\u03bd",
